item.title: About Me
item.dc:creator: jamie.deramus
item.content:encoded:
A Little About Myself:

Hi there! Thank you so much for visiting my portfolio site, Im thrilled to share a bit of my story and work with you. Whether youre here out of curiosity or collaboration, welcome!

Im a graphic designer with a passion for creating visual stories that resonate. From the time I could hold a pencil, creativity has always been my language. Whether it was sketching in a notebook, snapping photos with a camera, or mixing colors with a brush, Ive always kept my tools close, ready for when inspiration strikes. Even as a kid, I spent hours editing photos in my spare time, experimenting with effects and digital tools just for the joy of it.

Before diving into design professionally, I spent seven wonderful years as a preschool teacher, specializing in art and the Montessori approach. Those years shaped my love for creativity, education, and child-led exploration. I also worked briefly in ABA therapy, driven by a deep commitment to supporting individuals on the autism spectrum, especially meaningful to me as a parent to neurodivergent children.

Ultimately, my journey led me back to the creative path Ive always dreamed of. Returning to school to study graphic design wasnt just a career shift, it was a decision to fully embrace who Ive always been. Along the way, Ive expanded my skills into coding and website design, allowing me to bring both form and function to the digital experiences I create.

Through my work, I strive to craft meaningful, user-centered designs and to inspire my children, who are already exploring their own artistic paths.

If youd like to connect or see more of what inspires me, feel free to check out my work and updates on Instagram, LinkedIn, or reach out via email or social media. Id love to hear from you!

item.title: Home
item.dc:creator: jamie.deramus
item.content:encoded:
Hello and Welcome To My Page!

Design isnt just how it looksits how it works, how it feels, and how it connects people.

Hey there, Im Jamie, your go-to creative for all things visual and digital. Im a multidisciplinary designer with a passion for turning ideas into impactful, beautifully-crafted experiences. My journey started with editing photos just for fun in my teenage bedroom, and over the years, that spark grew into a full-blown creative career.

Today, I specialize in blending striking visuals with smart design, whether that means building responsive websites, crafting bold brand identities, or capturing moments through photography. I dont just make things look good, I make them work seamlessly and tell a story.

Whether youre looking for a polished logo, a scroll-stopping website, custom photo work, or a design that simply gets you, Im here to help bring your vision to life, strategically and stylishly.

What I Do

  • Graphic Design
  • Photography & Photo Editing
  • Website Design
  • Front-End Development
  • Branding & Logo Design
  • UX/UI Prototyping

Thanks so much for stopping by!

Whether you're here to browse my work, collaborate on a project, or just get inspired, Im glad youre here. Dive in and explore, and if something sparks your interest, lets connect!

item.title: Questions and Testimonials
item.dc:creator: jamie.deramus
item.content:encoded:
FAQ's

Q: What services do you offer through your portfolio?


A: I specialize in a range of creative services, including graphic design, UX/UI design, branding, website mockups, and visual content creation. Whether you're looking for a full design solution or need help with a specific project, I can tailor my work to fit your needs.

Q: What design tools do you use?


A: I primarily use Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign) and Figma for digital design and prototyping. I'm also experienced with Canva, Lightroom, and Visual Studio Code for web-related projects.

Q: How long does a typical project take?


A: Timelines can vary based on the size and scope of the project. Small design tasks might take a few days, while larger branding or web design projects can take 13 weeks. I always provide a timeline estimate before starting any work.

Q: Are you available for freelance or collaborative projects?


A: Yes, Im open to freelance opportunities, internships, and collaborative design work. Feel free to reach out via my contact form with the details of your project.

Have Another Question? Ask Away!
